This spontaneous report was received from a consumer or other non health professional (patient's mother) via 
Rocky Mountain Poison and Drug Center (MCN15-000077) and concerns a 4-year-old male patient from the United
States: 017426405A.
Initial information was processed along with additional information received on 14-DEC-2015.
The patient's height, weight and medical history were not reported.
The patient was treated with paracetamol (suspension, oral, batch 981350-INV, expiry 04-FEB-2017, unspecified 
dose) initiated on an unspecified date for fever. Concomitant medications were not reported.
The mother reported that her 4.5 year old son started paracetamol suspension at an unspecified dose, and 
frequency on an unspecified date for a fever. The patient had received 4 unspeciifed doses from this bottle of 
